Founder Guru Nanak summed up Sikhism as to meditate on the Holy Name, to work honestly, and to share one's fruits with those in need. Enough said, but if you want to know more about the fifth-largest organized religion, do consult these books... or go here: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikhism.

